# Arroz con Gandules

> Arroz con Gandules is a traditional Puerto Rican dish that is served usually around Christmas season or special occasions. #side

![](56AEF472-3C6D-4051-8D11-F0DC36F85ECD.jpeg)

- Olive Oil | 1 tbsp | Or Pernil drippings
- Ham Steak | 1/2 cup | Cubed

Heat the olive oil in a 6-quart Dutch oven on medium heat until it shimmers. Add the chopped ham and sauté for 1 minute.

- Sofrito | Green, 3 tbsp | 
- Tomato Sauce | 2 tbsp | 

Add sofrito and tomato sauce and cook for a minute more.

- Sazón | 2 packets | 
- Adobo | 1 tbsp, 1 tsp | Maybe a touch less next time (2/9/25)
- Cumin | 1/2 tsp | 

Add seasoning

- Alcaparrado | 2 tbsp, Chopped green olives in a jar | 
- Gandules | Canned, 32 oz | 1 can drained, the other with liquid
- Rice | Long grain, 4 cups | Rinsed and Strained
- Stock | Chicken, 4 cups | 

Add the rice, water, olives, and pigeon peas.

Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook uncovered stirring every few minutes until all liquid is absorbed.

Reduce heat to low and cover with foil then place lid over foil.

Check every 15 minutes until dry. Fluff and serve.
